---
title: AmpMod Privacy Policy
---

*Last updated: 2025-08-23*

The AmpMod project respects your privacy. Every website says this, but we mean it.
For the purpose of transparency, here is a list of every place where and how your data may be used.

## AmpMod website
The AmpMod website does not collect any personal information.
The only data collected is anonymous usage data, which is used to improve the website.
These analytics do not use cookies and do not track you across other websites.

A cookie is used to store your session so that you can stay logged in.
This cookie is not used for any other purpose and is not shared with any third parties.

## AmpMod editor
The AmpMod editor does not collect any personal information.
However, the editor can load projects from Scratch's servers. We ask you to read Scratch's
[privacy policy](https://scratch.mit.edu/privacy_policy) to understand how your data is used when you load a project from Scratch.

The AmpMod editor is hosted on Codeberg. See their [privacy policy](https://codeberg.org/codeberg/org/src/PrivacyPolicy.md).
